Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.78,0:00:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for the last 35 years.\NI've worked in the field of psychoanalysis, all kinds of psychotherapy,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.35,0:00:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,done research on the relationship between nutrition and brain chemistry\Nand its relationship to emotions and emotional and mental disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.82,0:00:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the last 10 years, I've been doing research on the nature of consciousness itself\Nand its extensions into that field of knowledge man calls spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.95,0:00:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In our talk today, we'll be talking about how to meet the major crises of life.\NDeath, divorce, separation, disfigurement, injury, accident, catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.54,0:00:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Those serious things which result in emotional overwhelms.\NWhat techniques can we utilize to handle these experiences?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.56,0:01:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And in doing that, we'll be referring, as we have in these other talks,\Nto a map of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A map of consciousness, which gives us a point of reference\Nand allows us a greater understanding of what we'll be talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.73,0:01:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this map, you'll see it's a mathematical model.\NWithin the box, this represents the human ego, the self with a small self,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.87,0:01:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,are various levels of consciousness.\NAnd they're named according to common human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.31,0:01:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt and apathy and grief and fear, desire, anger, pride, courage,\Nwillingness, acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.42,0:01:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Love, joy.\NAs we get towards the top, we reach, we get closer and closer to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.14,0:01:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we get to the bottom, we get farther and farther from the truth.\NAnd you'll notice that death is calibrated at zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.70,0:01:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment at 600.\NAnd so these numbers indicate the relative energies, the power of these energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:02:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So that apathy is, for instance, half as powerful as fear.\NFear has half the energy of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.81,0:02:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And neutral has half the energy of love.\NAnd so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.34,0:02:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that we can get a feeling for the relative power of these different positions.\NThey're really coming out of points of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that there are arrows.\NSo that everything below courage, you'll notice all the arrows go to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.25,0:02:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Indicating that the effect is destructive, that the effect is anti-life,\Ndoes not support life, and is in violation of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.53,0:02:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NAnd when we pass above the level of truth, which is courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.11,0:02:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll notice that the needle swings to the middle.\NAnd as we get beyond that, into areas of lovingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.50,0:02:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll notice that the arrows go to the right.\NIndicating that these energy fields nurture and support life, and are aligned with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.71,0:03:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the subject for today, acute catastrophic experiences, which are overwhelming,\Nwe'll be referring to these energy fields then,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.31,0:03:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for a greater understanding.\NBecause we'll be talking about techniques with which to handle these emotional overwhelms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.74,0:03:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In these experiences, life suddenly becomes a nightmare.\NWhen it's suddenly overwhelmed by an emotional storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.15,0:03:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How to handle this acute event.\NHow to shorten the period, and how to relieve the pain and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.34,0:03:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Diminish it to the minimum, will be the techniques we're talking about today.\NAll of these major life experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.34,0:03:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,have something in common.\NThey all represent, to the mind, a major loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.81,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,An acute catastrophic loss.\NThey all indicate a major change.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.18,0:03:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all have in common, the feeling of powerlessness.\NBecause of their permanency, the mind gets that it cannot do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.65,0:04:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That it is stopped.\NAnd it is this phenomenon of being stopped, the permanence, the fact that one is powerless,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and cannot change.\NAnd cannot change the event, that is partially responsible, for the acute upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And how to handle this, will depend on our orientation to the subject.\NAnd our knowledge of the whole field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.56,0:04:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these experiences, unleash a storm of negative feelings.\NShock, disbelief, denial, anger, guilt, attempts at undoing, self-blame, resentment, feelings of abandonment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rage at God and oneself, self-pity, rage at the world, rage at the family.\NAll these negative emotions surface and come on at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes in sequence, sometimes in combination.\NBut in general, there is a massive overwhelm of negative emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:05:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That they all share in common.\NThe acute separation, the acute sense of loss, the acute sense of overwhelm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the sequencing of first the shock, then the resentment,\Nthe disbelief, the anger. The sequencing of these varies from experience to experience and person
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to person. Their exact sequence is immaterial. What is significant is that they are unleashing\Nof everything at the bottom of the box. We said that everything in the bottom of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.81,0:05:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field, is in a negative direction. And when one of these energy fields becomes\Nstrong, it tends to pull the rest with it. So that grief over loss then seems to bring with it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.61,0:05:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt, senses of hopelessness, fear of the future, desire to change the whole thing, anger.\NThe whole negative energy field is unleashed in one giant emergency, and the emergency really is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.55,0:06:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,one of energy. The problem is really being that of being overwhelmed by a massive unleashing of\Nenergy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind tries to use reason. It tries to think its way out of this dilemma. It tries to find\Nexplanations and reasons. It can't succeed in this because the energy field overwhelm is so massive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.05,0:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that the thoughts become merely a reflection of the negativity of the energy field. And therefore,\Nthe thoughts themselves become negative. So now one is beset by an overwhelm of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.31,0:06:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,an overwhelm of negative energy. And then one is beset by the overwhelming of negative energy.\NSo one is beset by an overwhelm of negative energy. And now one is beset by an overwhelm of negative energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.25,0:06:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of negative emotion and an overwhelm of negative thoughts. How to meet this crisis is our talk for\Ntoday. Another thing that all these experiences share in common is that they are all at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.68,0:06:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of life stress rating scales. You know there are scales that rate numerically from zero to a hundred.\NThe degree of stress of certain life events and the ones that we're talking about today are all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.17,0:07:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at the top of the list. Death of a spouse, death of a child, death of a family member, divorce, all of\Nthese rate 100 on the rating scale. The other ones we mentioned rate maybe 95 to 96, 97. So the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.38,0:07:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about today are the maximal catastrophes which we can face in our whole\Nexperiences of life. How to convert these into acute gains, how to maximize them, how to use them
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.29,0:07:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as a springboard.\NFor a major leap in consciousness. We need to look then at consciousness itself and as we have in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,other talks we'll be talking about the relationship between body, mind and spirit. What is that\Nrelationship? What is its exact nature and how can it be helpful to us in our understanding of today's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.06,0:08:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,topic? And so we'll review again as we have in the other talks the fact that the body is unable to\Nexperience itself. The body has no capacity to experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.60,0:08:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes.\NIt just is. It is actually insentient. How do we know where the body is? Well, because of sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.64,0:08:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't experience the body. We experience sensations of the body. Sensations themselves have no way of\Nbeing experienced. They're experienced in something greater than themselves and that is in mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.24,0:08:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Our awareness of what is going on in body then is because it's being reported and experienced within mind.\NNow, mind itself has no capacity within itself to experience itself. That seems like a shocking thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But a memory cannot experience its own memoryness. A thought cannot experience its own thoughtness.\NFeelings cannot experience their own feelingness. It's because they are experienced in something greater than mind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:09:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is consciousness itself. It is because of consciousness that you're aware of what is going on in mind.\NMind then reports what is going on with sensations. Sensations report what is going on with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.57,0:09:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And so where we are experiencing then is several levels removed from the body itself.\NConsciousness itself is unable to actually experience itself. It is because of an absolute energy field beyond that called knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is absolute that we are aware then and know what is going on within consciousness which is reporting\Nwhat is going on in mind, which is reporting what is going on in sensations, which is reporting what goes on with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore where we experience, that which we really are, is considerably removed from the physical body itself.\NIt is because experiencing is going on within consciousness that we can address the solution to human problems
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:10:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,directly within the field of consciousness itself, thereby effectively shortening and relieving the amount\Nof pain and suffering and bringing about a far more effective result.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw the result of this technique and this approach in our talks on the handling of physical pain and sickness and suffering,\Nof depression, anxiety and fear. And the same technique will work in meeting these acute emotional catastrophic emergencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.08,0:10:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you actually live is in the experience of your own experiencing.\NA person thinks, well, I live in the world, I'm experiencing the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.89,0:10:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is coming in and it's being registered in your experience of your experience of it.\NWe can handle anything if we address then this exact focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.47,0:11:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If we focus on where we're experiencing experience, we can handle things with precision.\NWe can in moments and minutes handle things that would take weeks, months, years and in fact lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.71,0:11:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We can handle within an hour a thing that others have been unable to handle in an entire lifetime.\NWe know people who have had these catastrophic events early in life and we see them in older age and it's still not over with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.09,0:11:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The resentment, the bitterness, the anger, the disillusionment, the rage, the major decisions that come out of those negative feelings\Nare still with the person 50 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though the event happened yesterday.\NIt's still unhealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still undone.\NThere hasn't been the knowledge present of how to handle this overwhelm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.24,0:11:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so today we're talking about directly how to handle the overwhelm at the level at which it is being experienced.\NTo look at the experiencing, the field of the experiencing and to be aware where experiencing is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.26,0:12:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiencing is not happening out in the world.\NExperience is not happening in your foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not happening in yourself.\NIt's not happening in your stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.29,0:12:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening within consciousness.\NAnd as you examine where you experience experience, you'll find that it's everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.29,0:12:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't experience things in a focal point.\NThat's a belief system of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.29,0:12:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, if I say to someone who hasn't looked into this, where do you experience your thoughts?\NOut of habit, the person points to their head and says here, that's a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your thought about thoughts.\NYou think your thoughts here, but that's only a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.29,0:12:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think that thought, that your thoughts are thought here?\NAs you really go into it and introspect a little bit with a little contemplation and reflection,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.29,0:12:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that experiencing is diffuse, that it's going on everywhere.\NIf you had to put your finger on where is experiencing happening, you cannot put your finger on any particular place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.29,0:13:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like everywhere and nowhere simultaneously.\NAnd it is that particular point which we'll be working with today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.29,0:13:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In doing this, we'll say something surprising, but something that makes this kind of work precise.\NI know because I've worked with it clinically for over 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.29,0:13:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know because I've been through most of the major life crises myself.\NIn fact, in the last few years, I've been through half a dozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.34,0:13:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I will share my own experience of the truth of these things\Nbecause all of them can be experienced within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.87,0:13:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that you have to handle in these acute catastrophic events is the emotions themselves.\NThe energy of the emotion is the only thing you have to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.33,0:13:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds surprising?\NIt's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.41,0:14:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact that if we look at the experience, we'll see it's not the event that happened in the world\Nor that we think has happened in the world that is our problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.62,0:14:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way we feel about it.\NIs it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.62,0:14:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares about facts?\NFacts don't mean anything in and of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.62,0:14:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your emotional reaction to the fact.\NA fact is only a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.62,0:14:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nothing.\NIt's how we feel about that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so therefore, the only thing we really ever have to handle about the events in life is our feelings.\NOur feelings come from our attitudes, our beliefs, our way of being with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we view ourself and the world.\NSo that will give a variety to the emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.62,0:14:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But in an overwhelm, our problem is going to be handling just the emotional energy itself.\NWe don't even really have to handle the emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.62,0:14:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All we have to handle is the energy of the emotions.\NYes, you say, but what about the events out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.00,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to do now with no money?\NWhat am I going to do with no husband, etc., etc.?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:15:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly, the events are very easy to handle.\NThere is no acute catastrophe that the events themselves are merely just handled in a mechanical way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.45,0:15:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the feelings are aside, you may have reluctance, you may have some resentment, you may have regret.\NBut these are minor things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.45,0:15:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The handling of the actual issues within the phenomenal world, within your daily life, are going to be easy.\NThey're not the real problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.92,0:15:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought that they are a real problem is just coming out of the negative emotions.\NThe fact that they seem catastrophic and hopeless and unbearable and insurmountable is merely coming out of the energy field of the emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you come out on the other side of it, life adjusts itself.\NLife adjusts itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.34,0:15:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else comes in to fill the vacuum.\NLife goes right on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.40,0:16:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I go right on doing carpentry work even though I lost the thumb that was essential to doing it all of my life.\NThe problem is really not how am I going to learn to do carpentry again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.98,0:16:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is really not where am I going to start another business again.\NHow am I going to start earning money again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.98,0:16:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are simple.\NThose are simple once the emotions are out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.98,0:16:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Life presents the solutions to all problems.\NNecessity is the mother of invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.98,0:16:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever the dilemma is that appears in one's life, it will resolve itself.\NYou will meet somebody new.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.98,0:16:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of life resumes.\NLife goes right on no matter how major the catastrophe seems at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.01,0:16:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So our problem is not handling the event out there, not handling the circumstances of life.\NThey will handle themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.01,0:16:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, usually relatives will handle it for you while you are knocked out of the box by the overwhelm.\NThe problem then is handling the energies which are arising.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We said once one of these major negative energy fields releases itself, starts to unleash itself,\Nthat it tends to drag the rest with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.69,0:17:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarely do you experience grief alone.\NThere is also almost always guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.69,0:17:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief is associated with that.\NBlaming yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.69,0:17:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't I look, you know, as I went around the turn, why didn't I put chains on?\NWhy didn't I take her to the doctor sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.69,0:17:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we could have cured her cancer.\NWhy did I bet on that horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.69,0:17:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of a retrospective self-recrimination.\NThere is also apathy, hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.69,0:17:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is hopeless.\NLife seems hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.69,0:17:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like we will never be happy again, like the source of happiness has left our life.\NOf course, the grief is natural to the loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.69,0:17:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there are the fears that arise.\NHow will I live without whatever it is that I have lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.69,0:17:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The constant, incessant desire drives us crazy to try and change it.\NWhat can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.69,0:17:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The bargaining, the trying to manipulate, the arguing with God, the making bargains with God.\NOh God, if you only let so and so live, I will do this and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.69,0:18:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the anger, the rage at life, at the nature of life.\NAnger displaced onto the people of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.69,0:18:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the doctor's fault.\NLet's sue the doctor if the patient died.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.69,0:18:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The anger at the spouse for having disrupted the marriage and lifestyle.\NAll of these negative energies usually unleash all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.75,0:18:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And from moment to moment, one or the other may be dominant.\NAs we said before, at the same time, the mind is thrashing around wildly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.94,0:18:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to come up with explanations, trying to figure it out.\NWe are swamped by the overflow of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.94,0:18:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Overflow of energy.\NThe problem is that the energy is too much for the apparatus to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes into disorganization, into biologic overwhelm.\NAnd the acute stress throws the person into acute emergency emotions and an acute emergency state,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,especially to work in consciousness itself.\NThe problems are not best handled on the level at which they seem to be occurring,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.94,0:19:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but on the next higher energy level.\NHigher energy means greater power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.94,0:19:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Handle there.\NIt handles it automatically on the lower levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.94,0:19:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All we have to handle then are the energies of the emotional overwhelm.\NDoes that sound surprising for a psychiatrist to say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.97,0:19:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people would expect that a psychiatrist would begin talking about the psychology.\NThe psychology, the intricate relationship between the person and these events and what they mean symbolically.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.97,0:19:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The psychological components.\NBut we're going to bypass all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.97,0:19:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to talk about the fact that the emotions that are released, whatever the psychology,\Nit makes no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes no difference.\NWhat's happening is a massive release of these negative emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.97,0:19:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is it about the emotions that we're interested in is the energy of the emotions.\NAnd so the technique which we found very, very effective is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.76,0:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We ignore the thoughts.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the mind is never going to figure it out.\NThe mind does not have the capacity to figure it out and handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.76,0:20:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is in a massive overwhelm.\NThe issues are extraordinarily complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.76,0:20:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And to unravel it would take a lifetime if you really wanted to know the full significance\Nand every contribution from every level of one's psychological self to the total meaning of these experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't really have to do that.\NAnd it's a very good thing that we don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.76,0:20:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have to go into the feeling itself.\NNotice that the feeling is being felt in a general way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.76,0:20:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that the feeling has below it an energy.\NIt's as though consciousness works this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.79,0:20:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though there's a diffuse body of energy which really has no name.\NWe could call it the energy of emotionalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.79,0:21:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy behind feelingness.\NGiven a moment of time, this diffuse, unnamed energy will begin to take form.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.79,0:21:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It will begin to take the form, let's say, of grief or anger or rage or indignation, self-pity, whatever, jealousy.\NThis emotional feel which now has some kind of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.81,0:21:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see.\NAt first it's diffuse and formless.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.81,0:21:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But it now begins to take something of the form of grief.\NBut there's also some fear in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.81,0:21:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also some anger in it.\NIt's sort of diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of, we might call it, the energy of negative emotions in general.\NAllow it a split second longer and it will now take a greater form.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.81,0:21:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say a specific fear.\NYou know, how will I live now without money or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.81,0:21:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear begins to take form.\NAnd then out of the specific emotion, let us say in this case fear, thoughts begin to arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:22:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like a sequence of events.\NIt's like an ocean of suppressed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.81,0:22:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we'll be doing today is talking about how to decompress it.\NHow to decompress it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.81,0:22:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can cut the fuse, if we can pull the plug, then we've disconnected the whole experience.\NAnd we're left then with an inner state of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.10,0:22:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I'd like you to do today is to accept, to take my word for the fact that you don't have to do anything about the external events.\NYou don't have to figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.26,0:22:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make any progress by looking at the thoughts because they are endless.\NYou're not really going to get much headway in handling it by looking at the specific emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.52,0:22:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But you will get a very profound effect if you allow yourself to focus on the energy below the upset.\NAs you catch the experience earlier and earlier, you will get that this energy is diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.81,0:23:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost nameless.\NIt's like a container of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.81,0:23:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...pressurized gas that's seeking release.\NAnd this pressurized emotion, the energy of it, has been accumulating for a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.84,0:23:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the suppressed emotion that has accumulated up to this point in time.\NAnd it now has an out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.84,0:23:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the event that has happened in life has opened the sluices, has opened the gates, has opened the doorway.\NAnd all this container of compressed, suppressed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.84,0:23:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...emotional energy is now using this opportunity to escape.\NOnce the barn door is open, all the animals run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.84,0:23:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How to get out of the way of these running animals?\NYou can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.22,0:23:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to cut through it quickly is to accept the fact that you can't escape this experience.\NTrying to escape it only prolongs it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.22,0:24:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It would seem the mind will try to figure out ways to escape it as though that will reduce the pain.\NActually, the pain comes from resisting the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.22,0:24:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The pain comes from resisting it.\NAnd so we'll use somewhat the same technique we did with physical pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.22,0:24:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we surrender, we let go resisting this energy field.\NWe just sit down and let go resisting it and choose to be with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.22,0:24:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The faster we open it up, the faster we let that energy out, the quicker the experience will be over.\NInstead of dragging it out endlessly, agonizingly...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.22,0:24:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...over the hours and the weeks and the days.\NAnd the months and the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.22,0:24:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the whole lifetime.\NThe whole thing can be let go of.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.22,0:24:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember we said when somebody had an acute injury to their hand.\NLet's say a burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.22,0:24:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If the person stops everything and does this very same practice.\NLet's go resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.22,0:24:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just opens the door and welcomes in and says, in fact, I want more of it.\NOf the energy of that experience and ignores what goes on in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.22,0:24:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignores thoughts.\NBut allows themselves merely to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.22,0:25:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To experience this energy field.\NYour mind will say, well I'm experiencing grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.15,0:25:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a label.\NSo we'll say all thoughts are labels and they have no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.38,0:25:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, none of these things exist.\NThese are all labels we've put on things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.38,0:25:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that it is grief and the mind expects if a loved one dies.\NAutomatically it says, grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.44,0:25:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief is a label.\NMind having the power that it does over emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.02,0:25:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind having the capacity to give it form.\NThe belief that to lose someone is automatically therefore grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.01,0:25:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Gives form to the emotion.\NThe energy field of the emotions is actually form less.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.18,0:25:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But we insist that it's grief.\NIt then takes the form of grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.18,0:25:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody holds a gun to our head.\NWe're convinced naturally in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.56,0:25:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That this calls for fear.\NAnd therefore the same energy now assumes a somewhat different form.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.56,0:26:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Labeled fear.\NWe want to decrease the form of the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.18,0:26:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And stop labeling it anything.\NWe don't tell people, you know, I'm going through grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.36,0:26:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going through fear.\NI'm going through an upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.52,0:26:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Upset is closer to the truth.\NUpset is a general term.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.52,0:26:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's very hard to say what the emotion is in an acute upset.\NInitially what is experienced usually is a sense of shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.52,0:26:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of numbness.\NA sense of disbelief.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.52,0:26:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't believe that this happened.\NThat's the moment to begin this practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.81,0:26:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To know about it in advance, you're prepared.\NKnowing about it in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.91,0:26:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I recently, only a few months ago, went through such an experience.\NAnd instantly began letting go, resisting the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.00,0:26:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Constantly canceling out the thoughts.\NCanceling out the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.00,0:26:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The loss, for instance, seems forever.\NA lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.00,0:26:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a thought.\NIt isn't the loss of a lifetime that is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.17,0:27:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the energy of the emotion that's coming up about that.\NOnce the energy of the emotion about that dissipates,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.20,0:27:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that, let's say, you're never going to grow another thumb again,\Nis sort of a so what.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.20,0:27:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I've learned to do things with it.\NShuffle cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.32,0:27:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Count money.\NTurn the pages of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.77,0:27:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That would seem like an impossible loss becomes sort of a so what.\NThe problem is that acute catastrophic emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.16,0:27:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all we have to do is be with that.\NThe technique is to allow yourself to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.16,0:27:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, to get it over with in a hurry, just ask for more.\NSay to yourself, I want more of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.16,0:27:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I want more of it.\NWe'll see as we talk later in our discussion about the energy fields here,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.34,0:27:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is a major opportunity.\NThe cause of all pain and suffering is the accumulation of this compressed energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.48,0:28:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And life events allow us an excuse.\NIt opens the gate so that we allow ourselves to feel some of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.48,0:28:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We put some of this on a...\NLet's say somebody bumps the fender of your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.48,0:28:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All the suppressed anger that you've accumulated over your lifetime\Nnow has an excuse to pop out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.48,0:28:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets angry over the dented fender.\NIt gets annoyed over this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.48,0:28:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes into self-pity.\NIt goes into jealousy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.48,0:28:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The events in life are the excuses.\NExcuses, and what were their excuses?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.47,0:28:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the compressed energy field,\Nthe compressed energy becomes unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.78,0:28:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind then finds a way for it to discharge that is acceptable to you.\NA person who is familiar with this will feel the compressed energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.85,0:28:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to release it without waiting for the mind to create an excuse\Nthat justifies the release of this energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.85,0:28:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The more sophisticated mind doesn't need an event out there to release its angriness.\NIt just knows that it's building up some suppressed angriness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.85,0:29:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and it sits down and it says,\NI better look at this,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.85,0:29:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and starts letting go the energy of it\Nbefore the mind gets around and has to create something out there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.85,0:29:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to relieve itself.\NIt's as though the events in our life are almost like safety valves,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.85,0:29:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,release valves,\Na way to decompress this energy tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.85,0:29:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And so our technique today is one of decompression.\NIt's looking at the energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.85,0:29:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at it where it's being experienced.\NWe don't have to handle the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.85,0:29:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to handle the problems that the mind creates now\Naround this particular event.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.01,0:29:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at any life experience,\Nyou'll see you only live within your feelings about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.01,0:29:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The life event itself is really a nothing.\NIn the morning, it may look catastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.10,0:29:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,By noon, it might be amusing.\NThe event hasn't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.10,0:29:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The dented fender at the moment that it happens may be an outrage,\Nand you're in indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.10,0:30:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then as you think about it,\Nyou start to feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.10,0:30:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know very well you turned a little too sharply yourself.\NMaybe an hour later, you're feeling sorry for the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.21,0:30:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He now has an insurance problem.\NYou realize it really wasn't his fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.21,0:30:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you have a desire to make it up to him.\NNow you're feeling guilty and blaming yourself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.21,0:30:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you think about it again, and now you go back into rage.\NYou see what you're living with.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.21,0:30:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you living with the dented fender?\NThe fact is you never really live with the dented fender.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.21,0:30:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You only live with your own inner experience of that.\NIt's how you are with that that you are experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.21,0:30:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We never experience the dented fenders in life.\NWe only experience our emotions about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.21,0:30:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that simplifies it.\NIt makes it simple, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.36,0:30:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not quite as bad and overwhelmed now when you look at it.\NThe only thing you're ever going to have to handle is an energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.36,0:30:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that subtle inner feelingness,\Nletting go, resisting it, surrendering to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.36,0:31:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,welcoming it, saying yes to it,\Nreleases the energy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.36,0:31:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,After you do this for a few minutes or maybe an hour,\Ndepends on how adept, some people get it right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.65,0:31:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,other people it takes a little practice.\NBut as you sort of get where it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.65,0:31:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you no longer have to even experience the emotion.\NYou don't have to handle or experience any of these emotions as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.65,0:31:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That which was fear disappears and is not felt as fear anymore.\NAnger is not felt as anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.05,0:31:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Guiltiness is not felt as guilt per se.\NIt is felt as an overwhelming upcoming flow of a negative energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.05,0:31:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which actually is nameless.\NWhen you stop naming it anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.05,0:31:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you stop labeling it,\Nwhen you stop calling it anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.05,0:31:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you stop putting constructions of the mind onto it,\Nwhen you stop putting interpretations onto it,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.05,0:32:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you let go of right and wrong,\Nlet go wanting to make it wrong, the event wrong, yourself wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.05,0:32:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you bypass all that and go directly to the energy of the feelingness of it,\Nyou'll see you don't have to handle all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.05,0:32:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to handle the thoughts about it.\NYou don't even have to handle the emotions of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.19,0:32:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is handle this upcoming energy.\NCan you do that? Yes, you can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.19,0:32:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're doing it all the time anyway.\NThe ineffective technique of wildly racing around in your mind trying to figure it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.22,0:32:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,wildly running around inside your mind trying to handle these catastrophic emotions,\Nat the same time this letting go of the energy field is happening anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.60,0:32:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So today all we're trying to do is become conscious of it,\Ncut through the confusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.60,0:32:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,get right to the essential point of that which is effective.\NAll the dealing with the thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.60,0:32:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all the dealing with the events,\Nall the reasoning and figuring it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.60,0:33:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all the logic,\Nall the probing into the psychological significance and all that is entertaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.60,0:33:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's thoroughly ineffective.\NIt's a waste of time and energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.60,0:33:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It really delays the recovery.\NThe healing of an acute burn of the hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.60,0:33:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how long does that take?\NIt takes a matter of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.60,0:33:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How long should it take bleeding to stop once you cut off,\Nlet's say, a thumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.60,0:33:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually a matter of seconds.\NGoing instantly into this technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.85,0:33:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance when I cut the thumb off,\Nthe bleeding led exactly eight drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.85,0:33:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant releasing of it,\Nthe releasing of the pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.85,0:33:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the letting go,\Nthe resistance of the catastrophic overwhelm,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.85,0:33:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed the thing to stop instantaneously.\NAnd those people who tried this technique have had the same experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.33,0:33:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that on the physical level you can demonstrate the truth of what we're talking about.\NYou can do it with any emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.38,0:33:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You go into the emotion,\Nthen you go past the emotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.38,0:33:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop calling it anything,\Nyou get in touch with the energy of it that's coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.38,0:34:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be coming right up through your solar plexus,\Nor it seems to be everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.38,0:34:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You go right to where experience is being experienced.\NYou have to use a little discipline with your mind now and refuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.38,0:34:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you can refuse to have your mind fool you.\NThe person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.46,0:34:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,well I'm experiencing the death of that person out there.\NYou're not experiencing it out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.46,0:34:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you're experiencing it in here.\NWhere are you experiencing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.46,0:34:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're experiencing it in here.\NThe same place that you always experience experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.46,0:34:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It is within your feeling self.\NYour problem is only your own feelingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.46,0:34:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is not the death of someone out there,\Nthe problem is not out there at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.46,0:34:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're up against is the energy of one's own feelingness,\Nthe overwhelm of the energy of the feelingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.46,0:34:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we direct our attention there and focus it there with precision,\Nthat which could be a prolonged and very painful experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.46,0:34:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is aborted,\Nbrought to an abrupt end.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.01,0:35:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens if we keep on letting go of this energy?\NWhat happens if we welcome it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.01,0:35:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we say,\Nwhat an opportunity to decompress all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.01,0:35:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What will be the experience then?\NIt will be relatively brief,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.11,0:35:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively brief as compared to what it would be\Nwith an ordinary state of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.11,0:35:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens then is suddenly this energy field stops.\NIt's as though the decompression chamber,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.11,0:35:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the pressure dial reaches a certain point,\Nand when it reaches that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.46,0:35:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the overflow stops.\NAnd then one has a state of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.94,0:35:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Of peace.\NRight out of acute catastrophe come profound states of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.94,0:35:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And those who have been through it know what I mean.\NThe agony all of a sudden stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.98,0:35:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead there is almost a silence,\Nan infinite presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.98,0:35:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite state of peace.\NSomething that may be greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.98,0:36:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,greater than any experience you've had in your life before.\NWhen we come out on the other side of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.98,0:36:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not the same.\NWe're lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.98,0:36:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we're freer,\Nwe're less subject to pain within our own emotional experience henceforth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.98,0:36:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinically,\Nusually what happens is the person now sighs with relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.67,0:36:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They realize that life is going to go on,\Nthat they can live with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.67,0:36:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As bad as it seemed,\Nsomehow one can survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.67,0:36:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the period of peace goes on for a variable period of time,\Nand then there will be a wave of this emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.67,0:36:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and personality coming back.\NIt tends to come back in waves with periods of relief in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.67,0:36:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we do is when the wave comes,\Nwe welcome it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.67,0:36:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to release as much out of this valve as we can\Nbefore it shuts off again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.96,0:36:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome it as a very valuable opportunity.\NOne that may not happen too many times in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.05,0:36:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,One to be treasured.\NThe treasuring of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.05,0:36:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of it,\Nonly comes when you're really on the other side of the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.05,0:36:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can look back on it now\Nwith the wisdom that you've gained.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.05,0:37:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that the mind is not going to really be of any help\Nin this experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.05,0:37:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the mind is looking in the wrong direction.\NThe mind is saying to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.05,0:37:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if I could only change the circumstances\Nor the event out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.05,0:37:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then I would feel all right.\NWell, we have some good clinical examples of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.13,0:37:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We've talked in some of these other talks\Nabout a clinical case I had
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.13,0:37:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of a woman who received a telegram\Nthat her son was killed in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.13,0:37:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what happened is she stopped talking\Nand she sat in a rocking chair near the window
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.53,0:37:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and she just kept rocking back and forth\Nand staring numbly out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.53,0:37:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And she was in a state here that we call apathy.\NComplete loss of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.63,0:37:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The world looked hopeless\Nand to her, God was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.63,0:37:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She rocked back and forth in this hopeless state\Nand didn't respond verbally to the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.80,0:37:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Refused to eat.\NBarely slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.80,0:38:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Took naps perhaps during the night.\NBut just stared blankly out the window
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.80,0:38:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in a total state of apathy.\NAnd we said that certain changes had taken place
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.80,0:38:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in her brain chemistry as a result of this\Nand the neurotransmitters being depleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.80,0:38:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Some, I think it was about a week or ten days later,\Nthe family in the meantime didn't know what to do with this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.09,0:38:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and was, of course, very disturbed.\NAnd about a week or ten days later,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.09,0:38:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the family received another telegram from the State Department\Nsaying that it was all a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.09,0:38:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That the son had not been killed in action.\NIt was another serviceman with the same name
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.09,0:38:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and curiously a number that was only one digit off.\NSomehow there'd been an error in the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.09,0:38:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they said to her,\Nmother, mother, he's not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.15,0:38:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And she went right on rocking,\Nstaring blankly out the window
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.15,0:38:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as though she didn't even hear them.\NSo changing the circumstances in the outer world
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.21,0:39:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are not necessarily going to change the upset.\NWhy? Because it has started a process.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.21,0:39:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the process now that has to be handled.\NSo what has to be accepted at this particular time?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.21,0:39:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the events that have happened out there\Nbecause that's just what you can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.21,0:39:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you can't do is accept the circumstances\Nthat have happened in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.21,0:39:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What you can accept\Nis to surrender to the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.21,0:39:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've got to bite the bullet.\NThat right now there are times
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.21,0:39:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when you've got to be with\Nyour leg is caught in the bear trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.78,0:39:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way out.\NAnd so what we surrender to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.78,0:39:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is this experiencing itself.\NThe necessity to sit it through,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.78,0:39:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to face it, to handle with it.\NTo surrender to the experiencing of the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.78,0:39:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And to use the techniques that we talked about.\NTo be effective then,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.36,0:39:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay attention to the mind.\NBecause the mind really has no solution to this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.36,0:40:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is saying\Nif we could only change those external circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.36,0:40:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is where people's experiences\Nwith prayer often come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.36,0:40:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not knowing what to pray for.\NLater on they may come out of it bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.36,0:40:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they were praying in the wrong direction.\NVery often the prayer goes in the direction of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.36,0:40:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,please undo that.\NPlease bring joy back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.36,0:40:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please bring my thumb back.\NPlease change what is happening out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.36,0:40:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A prayer in that direction\Nis very unlikely to be effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.46,0:40:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not?\NBecause the form of the prayer is like
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.46,0:40:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,dear God please let me be one foot shorter.\NIs the problem God's or is the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.65,0:40:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the lack of comprehension of how to pray?\NAt this point the prayer which says
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.88,0:40:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,please be with me\Nand show me how to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.88,0:40:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me how to surrender\Nand how to handle this experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.88,0:40:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The asking for the conscious awareness\Nof the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.88,0:41:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The asking God to take on the experiencing for you.\NNow curiously enough
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.94,0:41:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as you keep surrendering into this experience\Nas you let go resisting it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.86,0:41:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as you let go labeling it\Nyou are progressively surrendering it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.86,0:41:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First surrendering that attraction\Nto pay attention to the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.86,0:41:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and to do something out there\Nto try and change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.09,0:41:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the surrendering\Nthe willingness to surrendering the labeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.09,0:41:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender\Ncausing this emotional energy to take form.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.80,0:41:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrender to the energy itself.\NThe total surrender to the energy itself
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.82,0:41:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,brings you into an inner state\Nas you keep getting deeper into the surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.82,0:41:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that something is experiencing\Nsomething is handling the experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.98,0:41:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of this experience for you.\NIt's as though the personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.15,0:42:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,now withdraws\Nand the energy is being handled
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.17,0:42:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and what one can say is that\Nthe energy is being handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.11,0:42:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So those who prayer\Nthose who pray rather
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.11,0:42:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in that direction\Nto be aware of that which is handling the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.11,0:42:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you get deep into the surrender of the experience\Nyou will realize
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.11,0:42:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is being handled for you.\NIt's as though some energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.11,0:42:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,some infinite mode of existence\Nsome aspect of beingness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.11,0:42:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is handling it for you.\NAnd there comes the surprising realization
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.11,0:42:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that one was never handling it\Nat all to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.11,0:42:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That this was some kind of an illusion\Nthat it was projecting oneself into it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.11,0:42:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,giving it form\Nidentifying with it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.11,0:42:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that was causing the pain.\NSo the pain is coming from the resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.11,0:43:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the insistence\Nthat the personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.11,0:43:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its aspects has to handle it\Nthat it must do something about the experiences out there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.11,0:43:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sue somebody or change the house\Nor move to a different location.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.55,0:43:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As it surrenders that\Nand it surrenders its thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.55,0:43:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it surrenders its wanting to control it and change it\Nand surrenders to the inner experience
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.55,0:43:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and sees that eventually\Nas a great gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.55,0:43:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How can it be seen as a gift?\NOnly when we come out the other side of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.38,0:43:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll talk to those who are aligned consciously\Nin their life with spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.38,0:43:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What does spiritual work look like to you?\NYou sit back and you ask yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.38,0:43:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what do I think of is spiritual work?\NFor those of you who don't call it spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.38,0:43:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you might call it consciousness.\NYou might call it dealing with your unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.38,0:43:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or your super consciousness.\NWhatever you label it, whatever you call it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.38,0:43:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the nature of that?\NWhat does it look like to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.38,0:44:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've asked three or four people\Nwho spent many years at it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.38,0:44:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said when you picture spiritual work\Nwhat do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.03,0:44:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they see a person kneeling down and praying.\NThey see a person in church.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.03,0:44:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They see a person at a gathering\Nwith everybody holding hands
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.03,0:44:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody saying Aum\Nand picturing light in the center of the circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.03,0:44:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They picture themselves sitting with a book\Nand studying late at night
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.53,0:44:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,12, 1 o'clock in the morning.\NThey picture themselves listening to audio tapes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.57,0:44:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of well-known spiritual speakers.\NThey picture themselves at convocations
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.57,0:44:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for body, mind and spirit\Nand healing services.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.57,0:44:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this is a whole panorama of that\Nwhich the mind then encompasses
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.82,0:44:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and says that is spiritual work.\NBut then when faced with a life crisis
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.82,0:44:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's as though that is excused.\NThat is not spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.82,0:44:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is everybody studying this textbook\Nand looking at a picture of a guru
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.82,0:45:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and singing songs.\NAnd then there's an acute catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.82,0:45:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and we like bypass that now\Nand we resume our spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.82,0:45:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,after we've sued that son of a bitch\Nand after we've handled all these various things in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.82,0:45:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As a friend of mine once said\Nwell let's sue them first and then forgive them later.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.82,0:45:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though one doesn't really see\Nthe essence of spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.82,0:45:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What one doesn't see is that the spiritual work\Nhas brought up these acute crises
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.82,0:45:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought us into them\Nand that these are the opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.82,0:45:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where the spiritual work is happening.\NThe other was preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.82,0:45:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The other was gathering of information.\NThe gathering of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.82,0:45:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The deciding on direction.\NThe accumulating of spiritual knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.17,0:45:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then comes suddenly the moment of truth.\NThen comes the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.21,0:45:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The time to do it.\NWhen we take it out of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.21,0:46:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see people who have been in spiritual work\Nand around metaphysical circles for years and years
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.21,0:46:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing changes.\NNothing changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.21,0:46:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the same illnesses.\NThey have the same problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.21,0:46:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their personality is the same.\NThey haven't had any of these experiences of inner truth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.21,0:46:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that they hear about.\NAnd what is the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.21,0:46:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is when life brings to them\Nthe golden opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.21,0:46:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.\NThis is the time to make that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.21,0:46:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual knowledge real.\NThis is the time for transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.21,0:46:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the time to take that leap in consciousness.\NThese are golden moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.21,0:46:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Acute catastrophes are the times\Nwhen you make great leaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.30,0:46:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you face it directly.\NWhen you fixedly say,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.30,0:46:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not veer from this spiritual work.\NBecause now what we're really confronted with
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.30,0:46:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is real spiritual work.\NNot reading some pleasant sounding phrases out of a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.30,0:46:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not looking at the happy picture\Nof some guru with his robes and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.30,0:46:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We're right in the thick of it.\NWe're right in the teeth of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.76,0:47:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The teeth of spiritual work is when you're confronted\Nwith that which you cannot avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.76,0:47:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A direct confront that requires a leap in consciousness.\NAnd so these are golden opportunities.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.86,0:47:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Priceless.\NIf you see them as priceless,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.86,0:47:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,your willingness to be with them,\Nyour willingness to say, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.86,0:47:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Your willingness to go with it\Nno matter how painful it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.86,0:47:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then makes a giant leap in consciousness.\NA real advance in wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.86,0:47:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge and awareness.\NThat which you read about within the books
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.86,0:47:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then becomes your own inner experience.\NThere is something below.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.86,0:47:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotionality\Nthat is literally experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.17,0:47:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,this energy out for you.\NIt's literally being handled
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.17,0:47:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by something far greater\Nthan your own personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.17,0:47:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Were there only the small personal self there,\Nit would be totally swamped and obliterated
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.17,0:48:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by the energy released by these experiences.\NIt is because there is something greater
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.17,0:48:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,than the personal self.\NWhich is more than capable of handling it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.17,0:48:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows you to survive it.\NThe trick of the mind is not to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The trick of the mind is to\Ntry to change what goes out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.75,0:48:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to figure it out.\NFall back upon the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.75,0:48:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the intellect is not going to resolve\Nthis kind of a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.75,0:48:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you've dropped\Na big oak log on your foot
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.75,0:48:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and broken all the bones\Nacross the front of your foot,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.75,0:48:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going to be needed at that moment\Nis your readiness and your willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.75,0:48:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle that which life presents.\NThe having the tools,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.75,0:48:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the having the willingness\Nbrings about a very rapid healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.75,0:48:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the awareness and an acute overwhelm\Nthat you really can't handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.75,0:48:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,See, part of the panic is the realization\Nthat that which you think you are
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.75,0:48:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,like your own limited self,\Nrelatively powerless,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.75,0:49:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is no match for the power of this experience.\NYou're correct. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.90,0:49:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's precisely what's going on.\NThe limited individual personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.90,0:49:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot handle this overwhelm.\NThat is the precise spiritual value of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.94,0:49:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you really want to change\Nabout the experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.94,0:49:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see what you want to do\Nis change how you feel about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.94,0:49:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how you really feel\Nabout it and what you can know
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.94,0:49:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the feeling will come and go.\NThe event is not going to bother you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.94,0:49:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,after the feeling state.\NSo all that one has to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.94,0:49:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,through then is the acute upsurge\Nof this emotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.94,0:49:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of this emotion.\NThe events are going to take
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.94,0:49:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,care of themselves.\NThe desire, as you see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.94,0:49:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to change that which occurred out there,\Nthe desire to change
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.94,0:49:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,how you feel about it\Nhas to be surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.94,0:49:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The confront is there\Nand all we can do is say yes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.94,0:50:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to experiencing it through.\NDeath of a loved one, divorce, separation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.94,0:50:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,acute emergency, catastrophe, injury.\NThey all bring about
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.94,0:50:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a state of shock\Nand the shock is the same
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.94,0:50:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the precipitating event.\NThe shock is the sudden realization
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.94,0:50:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's powerlessness.\NThe fact that the will
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.94,0:50:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,has met a brick wall.\NThe shock that one is stoppable,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.94,0:50:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that one has been stopped,\Nthat the personal will
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.94,0:50:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot have its way.\NTherefore the shock,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.94,0:50:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization of this\Nis the same in all the experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.94,0:50:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that it is unchangeable,\Nthat it is permanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.94,0:50:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the shock.\NIt's as though you came up full speed
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.94,0:50:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,against a brick wall\Nand every time in life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.94,0:50:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when we come full speed up against a brick wall\Nit releases the same energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.94,0:50:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've been through more than one of these experiences\Nthen look back and you will realize
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.94,0:50:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is so.\NThat each time the state of shock was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.94,0:51:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience, the sequence\Nwas the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.94,0:51:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the feeling of sudden numbness,\Nthe state of disbelief
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.94,0:51:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Nthe unleashing of all the negative feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.48,0:51:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at the negative feelings\Nprecisely,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.61,0:51:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look back at some of the experiences you have\Nyou realize the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.61,0:51:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we've been saying.\NThat what you really experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.61,0:51:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of this.\NIs that not so?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.61,0:51:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You experienced the totality\Nof that negative energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.61,0:51:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning it would be here.\NIn the afternoon it would be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.61,0:51:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, within a minute's time\Nwe fluctuate back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.61,0:51:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a scintillating energy field\Nin which the form of the emotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.67,0:51:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is flickering\Nfrom anger to resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.67,0:51:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to self-pity to jealousy\Nto getting even to revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.71,0:51:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to hating God, to hating yourself\Nto hating your family, to blaming society
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.71,0:51:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,blaming the government, blaming the laws.\NThe mind is wildly racing around
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.86,0:52:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in this negative energy field.\NThe reason I mention this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.86,0:52:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is I want you to see\Nthe diffuseness of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.86,0:52:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The formlessness of it.\NThat it is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.86,0:52:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,like a whole basket of negative\Nenergy
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.86,0:52:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and we only have to handle the basket.\NWe don't have to handle all the little things
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.86,0:52:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that are flickering around in the basket.\NWe only have to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.86,0:52:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it.\NYou see, if we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.00,0:52:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's decompressing the all of it\Nbrings us rapidly through
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.00,0:52:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and out the other side.\NThat it's an inescapable experience
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.00,0:52:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to surrender\Nto the work that has to be done now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.00,0:52:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we tell\Nwhen that work is through?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.67,0:52:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we suddenly come out\Ninto that inner state of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.46,0:52:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We know people, as we said,\Nthat years later still have resentments
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.46,0:52:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and are still caught in some aspect\Nof that negative energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.46,0:52:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it wasn't handled\Nin the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.88,0:53:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has been unwilling to sit down\Nand handle it until
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.88,0:53:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's through, until it's over,\Nuntil it's complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.42,0:53:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason, of course, that people\Nare unwilling to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.42,0:53:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the pain involved.\NBecause they don't know the techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.42,0:53:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because every time they go at it\Nthey start again trying to change
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.42,0:53:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the events in the world\Nand the thoughts, the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.42,0:53:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind trying to figure it out.\NThey run into the same impasse.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.42,0:53:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So not having an effective tool\Nwith which to handle it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.42,0:53:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the work is left incomplete.\NWhat happens with
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.88,0:53:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the incomplete work then?\NWhat happens with the emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.88,0:53:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that were not released?\NThat which is left undone
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.19,0:53:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to express itself\Nin emotional attitudes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.19,0:53:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and begins to express itself\Nin the body in the form
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.19,0:53:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of emotional illness.\NSo the unconscious guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.19,0:54:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that was not let go of\Nover the catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.19,0:54:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that happened many years ago\Nbrings forth through the autonomic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.19,0:54:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,nervous system and the acupuncture\Nenergy system and connects up
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.19,0:54:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with something from mind.\NWe said mind, the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.19,0:54:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the intellect, of thinkingness\Nis here in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.19,0:54:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of the guilt then\Nor of the grief, of the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.19,0:54:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the anger couples\Nis some belief system in the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.19,0:54:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,about some particular illness\Nand results then
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.19,0:54:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in a physical illness\Nwhich in psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.19,0:54:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we would say is psychosomatic\Nin that here the contribution
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.19,0:54:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the psychological\Nis on the surface and quite visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.71,0:54:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the end result\Nof the unresolved
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.71,0:54:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,handling emotionally\Nof a catastrophic experience
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.71,0:54:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is often an illness\Nwhich may recur many years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.71,0:54:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The grief that was undone\Nat the time over the death
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.71,0:55:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of some family member\N20 years later may express itself
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.71,0:55:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,as that heart attack.\NThe way we know then
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.94,0:55:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that the thing has been handled\Nis when we feel at peace about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.94,0:55:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel complete about it.\NIt no longer recurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.94,0:55:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It no longer brings up pain\Nwhen we think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.94,0:55:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel satisfied.\NWe may regret that we lived through it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.94,0:55:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had to live through that.\NWe came out on the other side of it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.94,0:55:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a different kind of a person\Nand with that knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.94,0:55:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there comes a certain sense of peace\Ntelling us that that has been handled now.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.94,0:55:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophic experiences\Nis the seed, the very essence
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.94,0:55:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ultimate\Nspiritual experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.94,0:55:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Within it\Nand following it to its very center core
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.94,0:55:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and walking off\Nthe cliff totally
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.94,0:55:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the total abandonment\Nthe total surrender to the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.98,0:55:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the seed,\Nis the very core
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.98,0:56:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which the spiritual seeker\Nhas been seeking all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.84,0:56:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens in ordinary life\Nin many catastrophic situations
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.84,0:56:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is an incomplete resolution\Nof the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.84,0:56:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The not realizing\Nthe jewel-like quality
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.84,0:56:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the opportunity\Nthe being overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.84,0:56:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by the what-ness of it\Nlooking in the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.90,0:56:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times what happens is\Ndrugs are introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.90,0:56:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,altered states of consciousness\Nso the person is taken to the emergency room
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.90,0:56:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and what could be a crucial\Nspiritual discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.90,0:56:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes covered over\Nso the band-aids over the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.90,0:56:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the family\Ntrying to distract the person
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.90,0:56:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with watching television\Nand taking them on trips
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.90,0:56:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the distraction from the spiritual work\Nthe introduction of things
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.90,0:56:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that alter the state of consciousness\Nso that the person
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.90,0:57:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of running into the experience\Nruns away from the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.90,0:57:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The essential aspect\Nof the spiritual benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.09,0:57:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from running directly\Ninto the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.09,0:57:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a saying in Zen\Nto walk straight ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.09,0:57:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what.\NSo when this catastrophic experience
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.09,0:57:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,comes we center ourselves\Nright into the core of it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.09,0:57:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we say yes to it\Nand we begin to experience it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.96,0:57:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes what happens then\Nif we refuse to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.09,0:57:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,any band-aids\Nand I've had times in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.09,0:57:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with acute catastrophic experiences\Nwhere there were band-aids available
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.09,0:57:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and I refused them\Nbecause by then I had learned the value
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.09,0:57:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of experiencing it through directly\Nbecause it really prevents
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.17,0:57:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing through\Nof what we might call hitting bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.17,0:57:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that whole concept of hitting bottom\Nwhich is well known
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.17,0:57:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in handling many serious problems\Nsuch as alcoholism
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.34,0:58:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which means to let go\Nand let go completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.34,0:58:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see what happens with the mind\Nis in an acute catastrophic situation
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.34,0:58:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it tries to cling to that\Nwhich is familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.34,0:58:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It tries escapism\Nit tries distractions
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.34,0:58:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it tries tranquilizers and drugs\Nand alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.44,0:58:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,various ways of trying to\Nameliorate the situation
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.44,0:58:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than facing it\Nand working it through directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.69,0:58:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence of a catastrophic situation\Nis the discovery of that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.69,0:58:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is greater than\None's personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.73,0:58:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencing through\Ncompletely of a catastrophe then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.73,0:58:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,brings one into a connection\Nthat there is something within oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.73,0:58:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that has the power to sustain\Nno matter how catastrophic
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.73,0:58:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience appeared.\NSo one comes out on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.73,0:58:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of it as a greater person\Nthe awareness that there is something within
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.73,0:58:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a presence\Nthere is a quality or aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.73,0:59:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of life within oneself\Nwhich has the power
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.73,0:59:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to sustain one through\Nthe most seemingly impossible situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.73,0:59:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If the\Ncatastrophic experience
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.59,0:59:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is not worked through completely\Nthen we have certain residuals
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.59,0:59:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if you like half fall off the cliff\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.59,0:59:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,some people think they've walked off the cliff\Nbut actually we find that they were secretly
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.59,0:59:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,crossing their fingers and hanging on\Nto some little lifeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.59,0:59:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The abandonment to God was not really total\Nand so there is left a doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.59,0:59:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that doubt then\Nthere is the residual
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.59,0:59:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say the residual of grief\Nthe residual of fear of the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.59,0:59:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if there wasn't the experiencing\Nof something greater than the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.59,0:59:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self there\Nthen we may have an
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.59,0:59:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,end up with a limitation\Na certain crippling
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.59,0:59:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain inability to go\Nbeyond a certain point
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.59,1:00:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to participate\Nbecomes limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.59,1:00:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather lead a limited life\Nthan face that kind of experience again
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.59,1:00:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather never love again\Nthan to love and lose
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.59,1:00:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the saying is\Nit is better to have loved and lost
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.59,1:00:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,than never to have loved at all\Nbecause the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.59,1:00:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of loving this\Nputs us in touch with our greater self
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.59,1:00:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is greater than our own limited\Nsmall self
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.01,1:00:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the complete resolution then\Nbrings us into a conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.01,1:00:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,contact with something\Ngreater than our self
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.01,1:00:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the hundreds of thousands of people\Nwho have tried that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.01,1:00:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and left the record\Nthey all attest to the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.01,1:00:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that when they surrendered the small self\Nto something greater than themself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.01,1:00:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they came into contact with that\Nwhich they considered to be real
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.01,1:00:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own inner experience\Nof the spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.01,1:00:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,then takes it from book learning\Nto a profound inner conviction
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.01,1:01:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,this inner conviction then\Nout of that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.01,1:01:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,comes a willingness\Nto re-enter into life again
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.01,1:01:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to participate\Nto take the risk
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.19,1:01:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the chances\Nwhat is the inner experience
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.38,1:01:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting bottom\Nit's coming out of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.38,1:01:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this feeling of hopelessness\Nand despair
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.65,1:01:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is really happening\Nis the personal small self
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.65,1:01:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is saying\NI of my own self
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.65,1:01:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot handle this\Nit is out of the hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.65,1:01:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then comes the willingness\Nto let go
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.65,1:01:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender to something\Ngreater than oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.34,1:01:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very bottom\Nin the pits
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.34,1:01:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one realizes the truth\Nand accepts the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.34,1:01:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that I of myself\Nof my own individual
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.34,1:01:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self\Nmy own ego self
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.34,1:02:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,am unable to handle this\Nam unable to resolve it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.34,1:02:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,then the victory\Nand the success arises
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.34,1:02:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the phoenix arises\Nout of the ashes
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.34,1:02:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the despair and hopelessness\Nit isn't the despair
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.34,1:02:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hopelessness\Nthat's of the value
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.34,1:02:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the letting go\Nand the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.34,1:02:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the limitation of the small self\Nin the middle of the catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.34,1:02:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the person says\NI give up
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.25,1:02:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of free will\Nand the nature of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.25,1:02:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,being what it is\Nit is said
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.25,1:02:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that the great beings\Nthat are willing to help all of us
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.25,1:02:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,wait for our saying yes\Nand so it is the sudden turning then
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.25,1:02:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from the bottom of the box\Nto the willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.25,1:02:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to the acceptance\Nthat there is something greater than oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.25,1:02:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that one can turn to\Nand when the person says
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.25,1:03:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,no\None can turn to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.25,1:03:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and he becomes not just a free will\Nbut a person is
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.25,1:03:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he has already turned\Nfrom the beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.25,1:03:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,into the nature of the purpose\Nof the purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.25,1:03:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of the purpose\Nand he is now
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.25,1:03:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,given a new form\Na new form of faith
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.25,1:03:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a new form of healing\Nand he gains
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.40,1:03:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a new form of life\Nmoment came a great transformative experience, the spiritual power of which is evident from
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.96,1:03:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the millions of lives that have been affected by the energy that flowed out into the world\Nby this man sharing his spiritual experience. So letting go and hitting bottom then are
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.88,1:04:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,crucial. It is out of the awareness that one cannot change it, that one is limited, that\None is powerless. So the powerlessness then is the very source of the discovery of that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.63,1:04:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which does have the power in the universe. That power comes in and handles the experience.\NWe know when that happens because of the profound state of peace. Where there was agony, now
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.96,1:04:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a state of infinite peace and the ineffable awareness of an infinite presence.\NHistorically,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.23,1:04:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it has been a special case out of which a realization of the truth has arisen, but it\Nis not at all necessary. It is only one type of experience. Actually, spiritual work is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.26,1:04:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of this nature all the time. The person who is involved in spiritual work is always looking\Nat what is coming up in life, seeing what is coming up in life as the teacher, the grist
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.86,1:05:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for the millstone.\NIt is what is happening that represents that which is being worked on. So an acute catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.82,1:05:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then would just be a continuation of the process that is going on anyway. So the person\Nwho is intensely involved in spiritual work, then it would be seen as a golden opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.59,1:05:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,painful and regretful perhaps, and yet one of great benefit. So the essential nature\Nof spiritual work is remaining the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.78,1:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To remain focused on that which is rising from instant to instant, always looking at\Nexperiencing, what is experiencing, where is it being experienced, what is experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.75,1:05:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NThere's a meditative technique then which is one that is used. The same result comes
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.01,1:05:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,about.\NThe constantly letting go, wanting to control. The experiencing the quality of experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.90,1:05:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\Ncham
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.11,1:05:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the sudden coming into the state of attainment.\Ncolon
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.82,1:06:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience that it is being handled by some infinite aspect of oneself, hitherto\Nfore suspected perhaps, but not actually realized. The realization of the presence after that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.00,1:06:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes more and more frequent.\NOut of this experience then comes an ever-grating willingness to rely on that inner presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.78,1:06:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Less and less of a reliance on the smaller self. Less and less does the person look to\Nthis small self to handle life's problems. There's a progressive willingness to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.19,1:06:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to one's higher self, the progressive loss of identification, and the increasing identification\Nwith that presence. The willingness then to surrender life in all of its aspects to the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.94,1:07:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will of God becomes the very present.\NThe acute catastrophic experience then is a key learning experience, a key learning
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.51,1:07:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,experience in that we learn to go to the very core, to the very essence of the experience\Nto see what it is and handle it right at the level of experiencing, right within the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.92,1:07:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,field of consciousness itself. The willingness to surrender, to let go, wanting to change\Nwhat happened out there. The letting go of wanting to change the thinking about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.96,1:07:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to handle it with the intellect. The letting go of trying to handle it with the\Nemotions. The willingness to surrender to the essence of the experience without calling
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.57,1:07:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it anything, without labeling it, without putting names on it. The willingness to handle\Nthe energy field of it, to go directly to the inner experience. And the surrender to
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.61,1:07:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner experience.\NAnd is the open doorway to the experience of something greater than the small personal
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.01,1:08:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,self.\NEach catastrophe then is a repeat, the re-presentation of another opportunity for this great spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.42,1:08:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,learning experience. And therefore we hear people who have been through great catastrophic\Nexperiences express their gratitude. We will hear people say, although I wouldn't want
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.36,1:08:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to live through it again, I'm very grateful for that experience.\NWe refer back to Alcoholics Anonymous again, we will hear people say that they're grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.39,1:08:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're an alcoholic. How could a person be grateful for that which the world considers\Na terrible catastrophe, and a terrible progressive illness? It's because what they learn out
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.60,1:08:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of this catastrophe was of such a great dimension that the price was worth it. So if we handle\Nthis experience correctly, we will later look back on it and will say that the price was
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.78,1:08:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,worth it.\NTime for Dr. Dain Heer's Remote View of Transition and True Consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.78,1:08:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dain Heer's Remote View of Transition and True Consciousness. NTW.com.au.\Nthe reconnection with the essential core of our beingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.86,1:09:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization of truth, made whatever the price was worth, worth it.\NAs we grow spiritually and as we become spiritually educated,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.06,1:09:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes less and less to bring about the willingness to face this inner experience.\NWe might say that a person's bottom gets progressively raised.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.60,1:09:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A person doesn't have to go through agonizing pain\Nbefore they are willing to let go and surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.63,1:09:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more, there arises the willingness to do it on a daily basis\Nso that it becomes part and parcel of one's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.97,1:09:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The constant looking at how I'm trying to control things,\Nhow I'm trying to change God's will about how I'm going to try and change God and control God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.81,1:09:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to totally surrender at great depth.\NAnd so we see surrender occurs at different depths.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.47,1:09:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In ordinary life,\Nwe surrender a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.40,1:10:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Under greater pressure, we're willing to surrender more.\NWe realize that we don't have to put ourself under catastrophic pressure
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.40,1:10:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to be willing to surrender at great depth.\NThe transformation of personality,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.18,1:10:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole shift in one's spiritual position,\Ntraditionally comes from surrendering at great depth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.18,1:10:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we become interested in what does that mean, surrendering at great depth.\NHow can we surrender at great depth?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.18,1:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we surrender at great depth?\NWithout having to put ourself through a terrible emotional catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.18,1:10:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to accomplish the same spiritual work.\NBy seeing the essential nature of the process, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.23,1:10:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we become educated.\NOur position shifts and we are different in the way that we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.23,1:10:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're willing to be with life in all of its expressions.\NThat willingness, then, is experienced as an inner state of aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.23,1:10:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming out of that willingness to take the chance.\NBecause we now know that we are accompanied by something greater than that personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.39,1:11:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the personal self that has to handle what comes up in life.\NThat there is always with us that infinite presence,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.39,1:11:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,more powerful than the human will and ego.
